Franc Plunges Against Dollar, Euro as SNB Vows to Defend Currency Target

-- B y   L u c y   M e a k i n
-- 
2011-09-06T08:08:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/franc-plunges-against-dollar-euro-as-snb-vows-to-stop-it-strengthening.html
The Swiss franc extended declines
versus the dollar and euro after the  Swiss National Bank  set a
minimum exchange rate of 1.20 francs per euro.  The currency plunged 6.9 percent to 1.18672, as of 9:05
a.m. in  London . It dropped 6.1 percent to 83.50 centimes per
dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
